## LRU Cache in TypeScript — O(1) get & put

---

### Data Structure Choice

The classic O(1) LRU uses two structures in tandem:

1. **HashMap** (`Map<K, Node<K,V>>`) — gives O(1) key lookup.
2. **Doubly-Linked List** — gives O(1) node promotion (move-to-front) and O(1) tail eviction.

A singly-linked list would require O(n) to find the predecessor when removing a node. An array or queue alone can't do key lookup in O(1). The combination is the canonical solution.

Sentinel `head` and `tail` nodes eliminate all null-pointer special-casing at list boundaries.

---

### Implementation

```typescript
class LRUNode<K, V> {
  constructor(
    public key: K,
    public value: V,
    public prev: LRUNode<K, V> | null = null,
    public next: LRUNode<K, V> | null = null
  ) {}
}

class LRUCache<K = number, V = number> {
  private capacity: number;
  private map: Map<K, LRUNode<K, V>>;
  private head: LRUNode<K, V>; // sentinel — MRU side
  private tail: LRUNode<K, V>; // sentinel — LRU side

  constructor(capacity: number) {
    if (capacity <= 0) throw new RangeError('LRUCache capacity must be > 0');
    this.capacity = capacity;
    this.map = new Map();
    // Sentinels never hold real data
    this.head = new LRUNode<K, V>(null as unknown as K, null as unknown as V);
    this.tail = new LRUNode<K, V>(null as unknown as K, null as unknown as V);
    this.head.next = this.tail;
    this.tail.prev = this.head;
  }

  // O(1) — returns the value, or -1 if not found
  get(key: K): V | -1 {
    const node = this.map.get(key);
    if (!node) return -1;
    this._remove(node);
    this._insertFront(node);
    return node.value;
  }

  // O(1) — inserts or updates; evicts LRU entry when over capacity
  put(key: K, value: V): void {
    const existing = this.map.get(key);
    if (existing) {
      existing.value = value;      // update value in-place
      this._remove(existing);
      this._insertFront(existing); // promote to MRU
      return;
    }

    if (this.map.size === this.capacity) {
      const lru = this.tail.prev!; // node just before sentinel tail
      this._remove(lru);
      this.map.delete(lru.key);
    }

    const node = new LRUNode(key, value);
    this._insertFront(node);
    this.map.set(key, node);
  }

  get size(): number {
    return this.map.size;
  }

  // --- private helpers ---

  /** Splice a node out of the list */
  private _remove(node: LRUNode<K, V>): void {
    node.prev!.next = node.next;
    node.next!.prev = node.prev;
  }

  /** Insert a node immediately after head (MRU position) */
  private _insertFront(node: LRUNode<K, V>): void {
    node.next = this.head.next;
    node.prev = this.head;
    this.head.next!.prev = node;
    this.head.next = node;
  }
}
```

---

### Edge Case Handling

| Scenario | Behaviour |
|---|---|
| `capacity <= 0` | `RangeError` thrown in constructor — invalid cache is never created. |
| `get` on missing key | Returns `-1` (LeetCode convention); no side-effects. |
| `put` on existing key | Value is updated **and** node is promoted to MRU — no duplicate nodes. |
| `put` when at capacity | LRU node (just before tail sentinel) is evicted and removed from map before insertion. |
| `capacity === 1` | Works correctly: any `put` evicts the previous entry; `get` returns the single item. |
| Repeated `get` on same key | Each call promotes the node — it stays MRU, never evicted while being accessed. |

---

### Quick Usage

```typescript
const cache = new LRUCache<number, number>(2);

cache.put(1, 1);   // cache: {1=1}
cache.put(2, 2);   // cache: {1=1, 2=2}
cache.get(1);      // => 1  — promotes 1 to MRU
cache.put(3, 3);   // evicts 2 (LRU); cache: {1=1, 3=3}
cache.get(2);      // => -1 (evicted)
cache.put(4, 4);   // evicts 1; cache: {3=3, 4=4}
cache.get(1);      // => -1
cache.get(3);      // => 3
cache.get(4);      // => 4
```

**Complexity summary**: `get` and `put` are both O(1) time. Space is O(capacity).

# LRU Cache Implementation in TypeScript

## Data Structure Choice

An LRU cache requires O(1) for both operations, which means we need:
- **HashMap** → O(1) key lookup
- **Doubly Linked List** → O(1) insertion/deletion at any position

Using both together (the classic approach), the map stores keys → node references, while the linked list maintains usage order (most recent at head, least recent at tail).

```typescript
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────
// Node definition for the doubly linked list
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────
class DLinkedNode<K, V> {
  key: K | null;
  value: V | null;
  prev: DLinkedNode<K, V> | null = null;
  next: DLinkedNode<K, V> | null = null;

  constructor(key: K | null = null, value: V | null = null) {
    this.key = key;
    this.value = value;
  }
}

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────
// LRU Cache
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────
class LRUCache<K, V> {
  private readonly capacity: number;
  private size: number = 0;

  // Sentinel nodes eliminate null checks on boundary conditions
  private readonly head: DLinkedNode<K, V>; // Most recently used side
  private readonly tail: DLinkedNode<K, V>; // Least recently used side

  private readonly cache = new Map<K, DLinkedNode<K, V>>();

  constructor(capacity: number) {
    if (!Number.isInteger(capacity) || capacity <= 0) {
      throw new RangeError(`Capacity must be a positive integer, got: ${capacity}`);
    }

    this.capacity = capacity;

    // Sentinel nodes never hold real data — they anchor the list
    this.head = new DLinkedNode<K, V>();
    this.tail = new DLinkedNode<K, V>();
    this.head.next = this.tail;
    this.tail.prev = this.head;
  }

  // ─────────────────────────────────────────
  // Public API
  // ─────────────────────────────────────────

  /**
   * Retrieve a value. Marks the entry as most recently used.
   * Returns undefined if the key does not exist.
   * Time complexity: O(1)
   */
  get(key: K): V | undefined {
    const node = this.cache.get(key);

    if (!node) return undefined;

    // Promote to most-recently-used position
    this.moveToFront(node);
    return node.value as V;
  }

  /**
   * Insert or update a key-value pair.
   * Evicts the least-recently-used entry when over capacity.
   * Time complexity: O(1)
   */
  put(key: K, value: V): void {
    const existing = this.cache.get(key);

    if (existing) {
      // Update value in-place and promote
      existing.value = value;
      this.moveToFront(existing);
      return;
    }

    const newNode = new DLinkedNode(key, value);
    this.cache.set(key, newNode);
    this.addToFront(newNode);
    this.size++;

    if (this.size > this.capacity) {
      this.evict();
    }
  }

  /**
   * Remove a specific key from the cache.
   * Returns true if the key existed, false otherwise.
   * Time complexity: O(1)
   */
  delete(key: K): boolean {
    const node = this.cache.get(key);

    if (!node) return false;

    this.removeNode(node);
    this.cache.delete(key);
    this.size--;
    return true;
  }

  /** Remove all entries. */
  clear(): void {
    this.cache.clear();
    this.head.next = this.tail;
    this.tail.prev = this.head;
    this.size = 0;
  }

  /** Current number of cached entries. */
  get currentSize(): number {
    return this.size;
  }

  /** Returns keys ordered from most → least recently used. */
  keys(): K[] {
    const result: K[] = [];
    let cur = this.head.next;

    while (cur !== this.tail) {
      result.push(cur!.key as K);
      cur = cur!.next;
    }

    return result;
  }

  // ─────────────────────────────────────────
  // Private helpers
  // ─────────────────────────────────────────

  /** Insert node immediately after the head sentinel (most-recently-used). */
  private addToFront(node: DLinkedNode<K, V>): void {
    node.prev = this.head;
    node.next = this.head.next;
    this.head.next!.prev = node;
    this.head.next = node;
  }

  /** Detach a node from wherever it currently sits in the list. */
  private removeNode(node: DLinkedNode<K, V>): void {
    node.prev!.next = node.next;
    node.next!.prev = node.prev;
  }

  /** Detach and re-insert at front in one logical step. */
  private moveToFront(node: DLinkedNode<K, V>): void {
    this.removeNode(node);
    this.addToFront(node);
  }

  /** Remove the node just before the tail sentinel (least-recently-used). */
  private evict(): void {
    const lruNode = this.tail.prev!;

    // Guard: only sentinel nodes remain (cache capacity is 0 — prevented by constructor)
    if (lruNode === this.head) return;

    this.removeNode(lruNode);
    this.cache.delete(lruNode.key as K);
    this.size--;
  }
}
```

