### Edge Cases Handled

| Case | How it's handled |
|---|---|
| `capacity <= 0` | Constructor throws `RangeError` immediately |
| `get` on missing key | Returns `-1` (LeetCode-compatible contract) |
| `put` on existing key | Updates value in-place and promotes to MRU — no duplicate nodes |
| `put` when at capacity | Evicts LRU (tail sentinel's `prev`) before map grows |
| `capacity = 1` | Only one real node ever exists; sentinel guards prevent list corruption |
| Concurrent mutation | Not safe — document as single-threaded (JS runtime assumption) |

