# LRU Cache Implementation in TypeScript

## Data Structure Choice

An LRU cache requires **O(1) for both get and put**. This demands two complementary structures:

| Structure | Purpose | Operation |
|-----------|---------|-----------|
| **HashMap** | Key → Node lookup | O(1) get/set |
| **Doubly Linked List** | Track recency order | O(1) insert/delete |

A singly linked list would require O(n) deletion (can't access previous node). An array would require O(n) shifting. The combination of HashMap + Doubly Linked List is the canonical solution.

