# LRU Cache Implementation in TypeScript

## Data Structure Choice

An LRU cache requires two complementary data structures working together:

| Structure | Purpose | Why |
|-----------|---------|-----|
| **HashMap** (`Map<K, Node<K,V>>`) | O(1) key lookup | Direct node access without traversal |
| **Doubly Linked List** | O(1) insertion/deletion | Can remove any node in O(1) if you hold a reference |

Using a **singly linked list** would require O(n) traversal to find the previous node. A **HashMap alone** can't track recency ordering. Together, they give us O(1) for both operations.

```
HEAD ⟷ [most recent] ⟷ [older] ⟷ [oldest] ⟷ TAIL
          ↑                                    ↑
       evict last                        add here
```

