## Data Structure Choice

**Why doubly linked list + hash map?**

| Operation | Hash Map Only | Array/Queue | DLL + Hash Map |
|-----------|--------------|-------------|----------------|
| Get | O(1) | O(n) | **O(1)** |
| Put | O(1) | O(n) | **O(1)** |
| Evict LRU | O(n) | O(1) | **O(1)** |
| Reorder | O(n) | O(n) | **O(1)** |

- **Hash Map** → O(1) key lookup to find the node directly
- **Doubly Linked List** → O(1) node removal/insertion anywhere (we hold a pointer, no traversal needed)
- **Sentinel nodes** (head/tail) → Eliminates null checks on every pointer operation

