# LRU Cache Implementation in TypeScript

## Data Structure Choice

An LRU cache requires **O(1) for both get and put**. This demands two complementary structures:

| Structure | Purpose | Operation |
|-----------|---------|-----------|
| **HashMap** (`Map<K, Node>`) | Key → Node lookup | O(1) get/set |
| **Doubly Linked List** | Recency ordering (head=MRU, tail=LRU) | O(1) insert/delete with node reference |

A singly linked list would require O(n) deletion. An array would require O(n) shifting. The combination of HashMap + DLL is the canonical solution.

